<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}-{8}{y}={54}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+{6}{y}=-{27}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --3. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{3}}{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{3}}}{{2}}{\left({2}{x}+-{8}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{3}}}{{2}}{\left({54}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{3}\right)}{x}+-{12}{y}={81}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+{6}{y}=-{27}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{y}={54}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{54}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+-{8}{\left(-{9}\right)}={54}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{\left({72}\right)}={54}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={54}-{\left({72}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{18}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>